The price/earnings ratio (often shortened to the P/E ratio or the PER) is the ratio of a company's stock price to the company's earnings per share. The ratio is used in valuing companies.

  
    
      
        P
        
          /
        
        E
        =
        
          
            Share Price
            Earnings per Share
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle P/E={\frac {\text{Share Price}}{\text{Earnings per Share}}}}
  

Higher growth firms will have higher P/E ratios
Higher risk firms will have lower P/E ratios
Firms with lower reinvestment needs will have higher P/E ratios
